CatDescriptText: Related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 13, 1965, pg. 7, reads: "D.I.'s Plan - The fabulous D.I. Club, intent on plans for the annual benefit ball...a Mardi Gras affair, March 7m at the Hotel Hilton...listen while decorator Kenny Moore explains how he will make the Hilton Ballroom a scene of fiesta and fun. Pictured, from left: Juanita Drake, president; Birdie Dunlap, Alberta Thompson, Margaret Watson and Evelyn Christian.  Tickets are $5.00 per person. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Kenny Moore, seated in center of members of the D.I. Club including left to right: Birdie Dunlap, Alberta Thompson, Juanita Drake, Evelyn Christian, and Margaret Watson seated on floor, planning Mardi Gras themed benefit
